---

### Summary

Promote "The One Thing" from a plain `DueTodayRow` list item into a visually dominant hero card in `BriefingPanel.tsx`, and add the pulsing dot + left-border treatment to the existing desktop card in `Sidebar.tsx`. Two files, three tasks (including screenshot update).

### Metadata

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Complexity | LOW |
| Files to UPDATE | 2 (`BriefingPanel.tsx`, `Sidebar.tsx`) |
| Files to CREATE | 0 |
| Total Tasks | 3 (BriefingPanel, Sidebar desktop, screenshots) |

### Key Patterns Discovered

- **Mobile hero card already exists** — `Sidebar.tsx:954-979` has the full gradient-glow + pulsing-dot pattern; BriefingPanel should mirror it exactly
- **Color token**: `bg-error` does NOT exist in this theme — use `bg-ideas` (`#F43F5E`) which is what the mobile sidebar dot already uses (`index.css:26`)
- **`bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-primary/20`** is the correct gradient (design references `obsidian-gradient` which is undefined; existing code already uses this Tailwind equivalent)

### UX Transformation

- **BEFORE**: `theOneThing` mixed into the "Due Today" list with identical styling to every other item; desktop sidebar shows plain glass text
- **AFTER**: Standalone hero card with gradient glow, pulsing red dot, `text-3xl font-black` title, `border-l-4 border-primary`, due-time row, and hover-revealed Done/Chat actions; sidebar desktop gets matching dot + border

### Risks

- **`bg-error` trap**: Design spec says `bg-error` but it's undefined — plan documents to use `bg-ideas` instead (HIGH confidence this is correct)
- **Screenshot tests**: Must run `test:screenshots:update` and visually inspect all PNGs before committing

### Confidence Score

**9/10** — both target files are read, the mobile hero card pattern is a direct template to copy, the only judgment call is the pulsing dot color (well-documented).
